Installing from sources

   1. Unpack defcon source package
   2. Go to defcon folder and type "phpize && ./configure && make && make install"
   3. Make sure you have extension=defcon.so in your php.ini
   4. Add the configuration lines from above in your php.ini

Compiling Defcon into PHP

   1. Unpack defcon source package to $PHP_SOURCE_DIR/ext/defcon
   2. In php source root directory run commands: "rm configure && ./buildconf --force"
   3. Configure PHP with command "./configure --with-defcon"
   4. Run make && make install
   5. Add the configuration lines from above in your php.ini

